The paper discusses the security implications of using the memory protection unit (MPU) in embedded systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on real-time operating systems (RTOSs) and embedded systems, which are relevant to the categories of embedded systems (cs.EM), operating systems (cs.OS), and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper provides technical suggestions for building more secure embedded systems, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
